swL3MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 3 Network Management Information for the proprietary enterprise.

VrId.name: VrId
VrId.description: A number which, along with an interface index (ifIndex), serves to uniquely identify a virtual router on a given VRRP router. A set of one or more associated addresses is assigned to a VRID.

swL3IpCtrlTable.name: swL3IpCtrlTable
swL3IpCtrlTable.description: This table contains IP interface information.

swL3IpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.name: swL3IpCtrlIfIndex
swL3IpCtrlIfIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies the IP interface number in the swL3IpCtrlTable.

swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3IpCtrlIpAddr
swL3IpCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the interface. This object only can take the value of the unicast IP address.

swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask
swL3IpCtrlIpSubnetMask.description: The IP net mask for this interface.

swL3IpCtrlVlanName.name: swL3IpCtrlVlanName
swL3IpCtrlVlanName.description: This object indicates the IP control entry's VLAN name. The VLAN name in each entry must be unique in the IP Control Table.

swL3IpCtrlProxyArp.name: swL3IpCtrlProxyArp
swL3IpCtrlProxyArp.description: This object indicates enable/disable of the proxy ARP function for IPv4.

swL3IpCtrlSecondary.name: swL3IpCtrlSecondary
swL3IpCtrlSecondary.description: When this is true(1), the IP address is the secondary IP. When false(2), the IP address is the primary IP.

swL3IpCtrlMode.name: swL3IpCtrlMode
swL3IpCtrlMode.description: This object indicates the IP operation mode. other(1) - This entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain are determined by each of the following values. bootp(3) - The IP address will be set automatically from a BOOTP server. dhcp(4) - The IP address will be set automatically from a DHCP server.

swL3IpCtrlAdminState.name: swL3IpCtrlAdminState
swL3IpCtrlAdminState.description: The state of the IP interface.

swL3IpCtrlIpv4AdminState.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv4AdminState
swL3IpCtrlIpv4AdminState.description: The IPv4 admin state of the IP interface. The default state is determined by project. This state will only be effective when the swL3IpCtrlAdminState is enabled.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6AdminState.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6AdminState
swL3IpCtrlIpv6AdminState.description: The IPv6 admin state of the IP interface. The default state is determined by project. This state will only be effective when the swL3IpCtrlAdminState is enabled.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAddress.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAddress
swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAddress.description: The IPv6 link local address for this interface.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalPrefixLen.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalPrefixLen
swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalPrefixLen.description: The IPv6 prefix length for this IPv6 link local address.

swL3IpCtrlState.name: swL3IpCtrlState
swL3IpCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAutoState.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAutoState
swL3IpCtrlIpv6LinkLocalAutoState.description: The state of the IPv6 link local auto.

swL3IpCtrlLocalProxyArp.name: swL3IpCtrlLocalProxyArp
swL3IpCtrlLocalProxyArp.description: This object indicates enable/disable of the local proxy ARP function for IPv4.

swL3IpCtrlIpMtu.name: swL3IpCtrlIpMtu
swL3IpCtrlIpMtu.description: The MTU is the largest size of the IP datagram which may be transferred using a specific data link connection. The MTU value is a design parameter of a LAN and is a mutually agreed value (i.e. both ends of a link agree to use the same specific value) for most WAN links. The MTU range is based on the chip of the current device. The suggested minimum value is 1500 bytes. The suggested maximum value is the size of the jumbo frame minus 36. The suggested default setting is 1500 bytes.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientState.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientState
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientState.description: The object indicates the state of the DHCPv6 client.

swL3IpCtrlIpDirectedBroadcastState.name: swL3IpCtrlIpDirectedBroadcastState
swL3IpCtrlIpDirectedBroadcastState.description: The object indicates the state of the IP Directed Broadcast.

swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12State.name: swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12State
swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12State.description: Enable or disable insertion of option 12 in the DHCPDISCOVER and DHCPREQUEST message.

swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12HostName.name: swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12HostName
swL3IpCtrlIpDhcpOption12HostName.description: Specify the host name to be inserted in the DHCPDISCOVER and DHCPREQUEST message. The specified host name must start with a letter, end with a letter or digit, and have only letters, digits, and hyphen as interior characters; the maximal length is 63. By default, the host name is empty. When set an empty host name, means to clear the host name setting and use the default value to encode option 12.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState.description: The state of the Dhcpv6 Client PD.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixName.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixName
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixName.description: This object indicates the name for the DHCPv6 Client PD. If the swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDState is disabled, this object will be clear and can't write.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefix.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefix
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefix.description: The IPv6 prefix obtained form delegation router.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixLen.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixLen
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDPrefixLen.description: The IPv6 prefix length for the prefix obtained from delegation router.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6AutoConfigState.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6AutoConfigState
swL3IpCtrlIpv6AutoConfigState.description: The state of IPv6 stateless adddress autoconfig.

swL3IpCtrlIpv6AutoConfigDefault.name: swL3IpCtrlIpv6AutoConfigDefault
swL3IpCtrlIpv6AutoConfigDefault.description: When this is true(1), a default route will be installed into ipv6 routing table. When false(2), no default route will be installed.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientRapidCommit.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientRapidCommit
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientRapidCommit.description: When this is true(1), Allows the two-message exchange method for address assignment.

swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDRapidCommit.name: swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDRapidCommit
swL3IpCtrlDhcpv6ClientPDRapidCommit.description: When this is true(1), Allows the two-message exchange method for prefix assignment.

swL3Ipv6CtrlMaxReassmblySize.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlMaxReassmblySize
swL3Ipv6CtrlMaxReassmblySize.description: Maximum Reassembly Size of the IP interface.

swL3Ipv6CtrlNsRetransTimer.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlNsRetransTimer
swL3Ipv6CtrlNsRetransTimer.description: Neighbor solicitation's retransmit timer. The unit is set in milliseconds.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMinRtrAdvInterval.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMinRtrAdvInterval
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMinRtrAdvInterval.description: The minimum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from the interface. The unit is set in seconds. It must be no less than 3 seconds and no greater than .75 * MaxRtrAdvInterval. Default value: 0.33 * MaxRtrAdvInterval

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMaxRtrAdvInterval.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMaxRtrAdvInterval
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaMaxRtrAdvInterval.description: The maximum time allowed between sending unsolicited multicast Router Advertisements from the interface. The unit is set in seconds.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaLifeTime.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaLifeTime
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaLifeTime.description: Indicates the lifetime of the router as the default router.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaReachableTime.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaReachableTime
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaReachableTime.description: Indicates the amount of time that a node can consider a neighboring node reachable after receiving a reachability confirmation.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaRetransTime.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaRetransTime
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaRetransTime.description: Indicates the amount of time between retransmissions of neighbor solicited messages. The unit is set in millisecond.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaHopLimit.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaHopLimit
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaHopLimit.description: Indicates the default value of the hop limit field in the IPv6 header for packets sent by hosts that receive this RA message.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaManagedFlag.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaManagedFlag
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaManagedFlag.description: When enabled, it indicates that hosts receiving this RA must use a stateful address configuration protocol to obtain an address in the addition to the addresses derived from the stateless address configuration.

swL3Ipv6CtrlRaOtherConfigFlag.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlRaOtherConfigFlag
swL3Ipv6CtrlRaOtherConfigFlag.description: When enabled, it indicates that hosts receiving this RA must use a stateful address configuration protocol to obtain an on-link address configuration information.

swL3Ipv6CtrlDadRetransNum.name: swL3Ipv6CtrlDadRetransNum
swL3Ipv6CtrlDadRetransNum.description: Indicates the value of duplicate address detection attempt number

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlTable.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlTable

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlInterfaceName
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPrefixLen.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPrefixLen
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPrefixLen.description: Indicates the prefix length of this IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPreferredLifeTime.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPreferredLifeTime
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlPreferredLifeTime.description: Indicates the number of seconds that an address, based on the specified prefix, using the stateless address configuration, remains in preferred state. For an infinite valid lifetime, the value can be set to 0xffffffff.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlValidLifeTime.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlValidLifeTime
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlValidLifeTime.description: Indicates the number of seconds that an address, based on the specified prefix, using the stateless address configuration, remains valid. For an infinite valid lifetime, the value can be set to 0xffffffff.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlOnLinkFlag.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlOnLinkFlag
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlOnLinkFlag.description: When enabled, the address implied by the specified prefix is available on the link where the RA message is received.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAutonomousFlag.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAutonomousFlag
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAutonomousFlag.description: When enabled, the specified prefix will be used to create an autonomous address configuration.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlState.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlState
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAddressType.name: swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAddressType
swL3Ipv6AddressCtrlAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of the IPv6 address. manual(1): the IPv6 address is configured by user. dhcpv6(2): the IPv6 address is assigned by DHCPv6 server. stateless(3): the IPv6 address is assigned by router advertisement.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlTable.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlTable

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific DHCPv6 Client PD IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlInterfaceName
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the IP interface.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixName.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixName
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixName.description: This object indicates the name of the prefix based on which the IPv6 address will be generate.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlIPv6addr.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlIPv6addr
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlIPv6addr.description: Specify the suffix of the IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixLen.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixLen
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlPrefixLen.description: Indicates the prefix length of this IPv6 address.

swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlState.name: swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlState
swL3Ipv6DHCPv6CPDAddrCtrlState.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpCtrlAllIpIfState.name: swL3IpCtrlAllIpIfState
swL3IpCtrlAllIpIfState.description: This object indicates all interface function state of the device. (except the loopback interface)

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlTable.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlTable
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlTable.description: This table contains loopback IP interface information.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlEntry.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlEntry
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about a specific loopback IP interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlInterfaceName
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlInterfaceName.description: This object indicates the name of the loopback IP interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the loopback interface. This object only can take the value of the unicast IP address.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlIpSubnetMask.description: The IP net mask for this loopback interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlAdminState.description: The state of the loopback IP interface.

swL3LoopBackIpCtrlRowStatus.name: swL3LoopBackIpCtrlRowStatus
swL3LoopBackIpCtrlRowStatus.description: This variable displays the status of the entry. The status is used for creating, modifying, and deleting instances of the objects in this table.

swL3IpFdbInfoTable.name: swL3IpFdbInfoTable
swL3IpFdbInfoTable.description: A table that contains forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the switch in determining how to propagate the received IP packets.

swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.name: swL3IpFdbInfoEntry
swL3IpFdbInfoEntry.description: Information about a specific IP address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr
swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr.description: A IP address for which switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.name: swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask
swL3IpFdbInfoIpSubnetMask.description: A IP net mask for this interface for which the switch has forwarding and/or filtering information.

swL3IpFdbInfoPort.name: swL3IpFdbInfoPort
swL3IpFdbInfoPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which packet having a IP address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of swL3IpFdbInfoIpAddr has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that switch does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address.

swL3IpArpAgingTime.name: swL3IpArpAgingTime
swL3IpArpAgingTime.description: The timeout period in minutes for aging out dynamically learned ARP information.

swL3IpStaticRouteTable.name: swL3IpStaticRouteTable
swL3IpStaticRouteTable.description: This entity's IP static Routing table.

swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.name: swL3IpStaticRouteEntry
swL3IpStaticRouteEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy. Once an entry is built,it shouldn't be modified.That is,it just supports create and delete actions.

swL3IpStaticRouteDest.name: swL3IpStaticRouteDest
swL3IpStaticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask object is not equal to x.

swL3IpStaticRouteMask.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMask
swL3IpStaticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-AND with the destination address before being compared to the value in the swL3IpStaticRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the swL3IpStaticRouteMask by reference to the IP Address Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the swL3IpStaticRouteDest object is not equal to swL3IpStaticRouteDest.

swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState.name: swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState
swL3IpStaticRouteBkupState.description: The routing state for this route.The value SHOULD be primary(1), backup(2) or none(3).

swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.name: swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop
swL3IpStaticRouteNextHop.description: Specifies the IP address for the next hop router. An IP address of 255.255.255.255 denotes a Null interface as the next hop.

swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.name: swL3IpStaticRouteMetric
swL3IpStaticRouteMetric.description: Specifies the routing metric for this route.

swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.name: swL3IpStaticRouteStatus
swL3IpStaticRouteStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry resides in the table. active(4) - the nextHop of this entry exists in the ARP table. inActive(5) - the next hop of this entry does not exist in the ARP table.

swL3IpStaticRouteWeight.name: swL3IpStaticRouteWeight
swL3IpStaticRouteWeight.description: Specifies the weight value. Used for the weighted multipath.

swL3IpStaticRouteInterfaceName.name: swL3IpStaticRouteInterfaceName
swL3IpStaticRouteInterfaceName.description: Specifies the name of the IP interface.

swL3IpStaticRouteCost.name: swL3IpStaticRouteCost
swL3IpStaticRouteCost.description: Specifies the cost of the Route Entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlTable.description: This table displays the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry
swL3RelayDnsCtrlEntry.description: A list of information display the current DNS relay static table.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName
swL3RelayDnsCtrlDomainName.description: The domain name of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr
swL3RelayDnsCtrlIpAddr.description: The IP address of the entry.

swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.name: swL3RelayDnsCtrlState
swL3RelayDnsCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry is reside in the table.
